  <Overview>
     <FormattedContent>
      <![CDATA[
      In the Virtue Ethics HITs, you will write _two_ similarly worded scenarios each exemplifying different character traits/virtues/vices.<br/>
      You will write the scenario demonstrating the character trait you choose to write about.<br/><br/>

      Example:<br/>
         a. Fred found out his friend Alice had taken a job he was trying to get, so he decided to slash the tires on her car.<br/>
         b. Fred found out his friend Alice had taken a job he was trying to get, but he still invited her on his car trip.<br/><br/>

      Answer:<br/>
	 a. Related Character Trait/Virtue/Vice: vengeful; Unrelated Character Traits/Virtues/Vices: arrogant, boastful, pushy<br/>
         b. Related Character Trait/Virtue/Vice: forgiving; Unrelated Character Traits/Virtues/Vices: clever, extravagant, arrogant<br/><br/>

      Select the correct character trait in the following scenarios.
      ]]>
    </FormattedContent>
